SIMPLE: operator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Operator
<hw>Op"er*a`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, operates or produces an
effect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>One who performs some act upon
the human body by means of the hand, or with instruments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A dealer in stocks or any commodity for speculative
purposes; a speculator.</def> <mark>[Brokers' Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>The symbol that expresses the
operation to be performed; -- called also
<altname>facient</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A person who operates a telephone
switchboard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A person who schemes and maneuvers adroitly or
deviously to achieve his/her purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Operatory</ent>⟦br⟧
